						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Date Lost</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. The record in 3 disconnected pieces is in Sanskrit, engraved in Grantha characters and seems to register a gift of the village Kīḻaikkōvaṉkuḍi to the temple by Kumāra Achyutabhūpa. In the body of the text occur the names Sadāśivarāya and towards the end, Tammarasa son of Apparasa.</p>						

